<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Serena Williams reached the US Open quarter-finals once again with a three-set victory over Maria Sakkari on Monday.</p>

<p>The American number 3 seed, who is chasing her coveted 24th Grand Slam title of her career, took the first set 6-3 at Flushing Meadows against the tough 15th seed from Greece. </p>

<p>Sakkari improved after that setback and levelled the match via a tiebreak despite spurning two set point opportunities earlier in the set. </p>

<p>Serena Williams reached the US Open quarter-finals once again with win over Maria Sakkari</p>

<p>But Williams won 6-3 in the deciding set to send the six-time champions through to the quarter-finals. </p>

<p>Williams will face the winner of Alize Cornet and Bulgaria's Tsvetana Pironkova in the last-eight. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Sakkari (above) struggled in the opening set, which she lost 6-3 to the American champion</p>

<p>Williams is looking to win the 24th Grand Slam of her successful career to date</p>

<p>The Greek 15th seed improved in the second set, which she claimed in the tiebreak</p>

<p>But Williams won 6-3 in the deciding set to throw off the challenge of Sakkari after over 2 hours</p>
